PLANNED CHANGES TO IMPROVE SAFETY [§ 68.155(f)]
Buckshot Treating Facility management is committed to the following:
- Preventing incidents;
- Training our employees in correct response procedures in the event of an incident;
- Participating in community emergency preparedness;
- Addressing citizen concerns by fully explaining potential hazards associated with Buckshot Treating Facility operations and all steps being taken to prevent and mitigate incidents.
With these objectives in mind, this Risk Management Plan has been developed to provide information about our management of the risks associated with the natural gas treatment and liquids recovery process. Most importantly, we stress our commitment to ensuring a safe operation for our employees, our visitors, our community, and our environment.
